Yes, in PowermaxStatusMessage for example:
        byte[] message = getRawData();
        byte eventType = message[3];
        String eventTypeStr = PowermaxMessageConstants.getMessageTypeString(eventType & 0x000000FF);

        addDebugInfo("Event type", eventType, eventTypeStr);

and in PowermaxPanelMessage:
        byte[] message = getRawData();
        int msgCnt = message[2] & 0x000000FF;

        addDebugInfo("Event count", msgCnt);

So the int variant works for both byte and int.

