Yeah, this was my attempt to simplify the copy-and-paste instances of bit math. It's wordy but personally I find this approach (array of booleans) more readable than the previous:
            int zoneBypass = (message[8] & 0x000000FF) | ((message[9] << 8) & 0x0000FF00)
                    | ((message[10] << 16) & 0x00FF0000) | ((message[11] << 24) & 0xFF000000);

            for (int i = 1; i <= panelSettings.getNbZones(); i++) {
                updatedState.setSensorBypassed(i, ((zoneBypass >> (i - 1)) & 0x1) > 0);
            }

I've tested this pretty extensively and the result is the same. I'm open to suggestions though.

